values: I use the watson speech to text service to transcribe what you are saying, and the text to speech service to speak back to you. The conversation service is fed the transcript of what you are saying, and by using a combination of natural language processing, and rules which guide me to the correct responses, I am able to find an appropriate response for your questions. The retrieve and rank service is used when I am in agent assist mode, and is used to ensure that the information I send to a call centre agent is the most relevant information for the current conversation

values: The Voice Gateway is architected as two independently scalable micro services. To be able to deploy these two micro services you need a Docker environment such as Coo bur net ees or IBM Spectrum conductor for containers. This can either be on premises or in a cloud of your choosing. Note that although the voice gateway can be run in either location, the Watson services which it communicates with are only available in the cloud in IBM Bluemix. Would you like to know more?

The Voice Gateway supports two broad use cases. The first is a self-service agent which can interact directly with a caller using natural language. Self-service agents are built with the Watson Conversation service. The voice gateway can also act as a more passive agent assistant. In this mode, the voice gateway can listen in on a conversation between a caller and agent, producing a real-time transcription of the phone call which can be used to provide useful feedback to the agent in real-time.
